SIMPLE: memorandum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Memorandum
<hw>Mem`o*ran"dum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Memorandums</plw>, L. <plw>Memoranda</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L., something to be remembered, neut. of <ets>memorandus</ets>,
fut. pass. p. of <ets>memorare</ets>. See <er>Memorable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A record of something which it is desired to
remember; a note to help the memory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I . . . entered a <qex>memorandum</qex> in my pocketbook.</q>
<rj><qau>Guardian.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I wish you would, as opportunity offers, make
<qex>memorandums</qex> of the regulations of the academies.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir J. Reynolds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A brief or informal note in writing
of some transaction, or an outline of an intended instrument; an
instrument drawn up in a brief and compendious form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Memorandum check</b></col>, <cd>a check given as an
acknowledgment of indebtedness, but with the understanding that it will
not be presented at bank unless the maker fails to take it up on the day
the debt becomes due. It usually has <xex>Mem.</xex> written on its
face.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Memorate</ent>⟦br⟧
